                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "On Tue, Dec 27, 2011 at 10:01:03PM +0900, Kusanagi Kouichi wrote:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> On 2011-12-27 09:48:27 +0100, Petter Reinholdtsen wrote:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> > [Kusanagi Kouichi]\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> > > /proc/mounts is symlink to /proc/self/mounts. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "So there is no need to\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> > > replace /etc/mtab if it is symlink to /proc/self/mounts.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> > \n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> > There is also, as far as I know, no reason to _not_ change it, given > > that both give the same result. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " There is a reason to change it, and > > that is to make Debian installations more consistent to avoid > > surprises.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> > \n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> > Why should we _not_ change the /etc/mtab symlink from\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> > /proc/self/mounts to /proc/mounts?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> \n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> If /etc/mtab must be a symlink to /proc/mounts and an admin must not > change it, shouldn't policy state about that?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Policy mainly dictates best practices, and the state of /etc/mtab is really only dictated by one package (initscripts), and of course util-linux (which needs to support it). ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " Additionally, some\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "architectures don't have a /proc/mounts, in which case we still need to support a static mtab (Hurd). ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " The current situation is that we create the symlink if /proc/mounts exists, otherwise it's left static.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I agree with Petter that while /proc/self/mounts is OK, having things consistent across all installations is more important, and the end result is the same anyway, given that /proc/mounts points to /proc/self/mounts.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
